:: ABC {"position":"400,1300","size":"100,100"}
There is a short pause and then as Mr Watson tries to speak, he begins to faintly cry. 
(click:"cry")[<img src = "https://img.wattpad.com/4c1a23fdd0e2f7e2c53ae2f33f6f8c40744135b2/68747470733a2f2f73332e616d617a6f6e6177732e636f6d2f776174747061642d6d656469612d736572766963652f53746f7279496d6167652f683669452d524a7567714a6265513d3d2d3433303636313132342e313532626362323764373066303532633733343139303439313539312e676966">
This is a noticeable sign of Distress. You are now tasked with assisting this individual in distress.
How should you respond? 
Option 1 - [["Oh, no. I didn't mean to upset you! What's wrong?"|UnsuccessfulABC]] 
Option 2 - [["John, I can see you're upset. Can you please tell me what might've caused this?" |B_0]] 
Option 3 - [["Cheer up, John. We haven't even started yet."|UnsuccessfulABC]]]


:: B_0 {"position":"600,1300","size":"100,100"}
Well done. 
You have not matched or opposed John's emotional state, instead remaining calm, patient, and empathetic. That's really good. You've also addressed John's imediately apparent emotions, and asked an open-ended question to seek further information. 
(click:"seek further information")[
Through the tears and with several pauses, John opens up to you,
(text-colour:green)["I'm just not the same person anymore. I used to be fit and i could run forever. Now I can barely get myself here. I don't know what I'm going to do, or how I'll make any money. It's just endless appointments..."] 
There's another long pause. 
<img src = "https://64.media.tumblr.com/13f155ce4ce2f7a189277c5eda6a6ce9/tumblr_o0bw1dztTD1sodtrho1_500.gif">

How should you respond? 

Option 1 - [["I understand you're going through a difficult situation at the moment, but I'm not actually that kind of therapist. I can recommend someone to you if you need help."->UnsuccessfulB0]]
Option 2 - [["Would you like to structure the plan around restoring your running ability?"->UnsuccessfulB0]]
Option 3 - [["So, you're saying you've had some of your physical ability taken away from you, and your life has changed drastically recently. You're also exhausted from seeing various specialists and concerned about your financial situation going into the near future. Is that right?"|B_3]]]


:: B_3 {"position":"800,1300","size":"100,100"}
Well done!
(click:"Well done!")[You have successfully paraphrased John's concerns and sort clarity of your summary. 
This isn't the end of the road, but it's a great step toward gaining understanding.
<img src = "data:image/jpeg;base64,">]
(click:"gaining understanding")[You/Sherlock: (text-colour:yellow)["So, you're saying you've had some of your physical ability taken away from you, and your life has changed drastically recently. You're also exhausted from seeing various specialists and concerned about your financial situation going into the near future. Is that right?"]
John Watson: (text-colour:green)["More than the 'near' future, but yes. ...I can't do anything anymore."]

How should you respond? 

Option 1 - [["It must be very overwhelming to have such drastic changes to your life happen so suddenly." |B_3_1]]
Option 2 - [["Don't worry, John. I've seen people in far worse condition than you make impressive recoveries. What's money for, if you can't invest in your health?"|UnsuccessfulB3]]
Option 3 - [["I wouldn't say anything. We all have to start somewhere." |UnsuccessfulB3]]]


:: B_3_1 {"position":"1000,1300","size":"100,100"}
You're doing great at this!
(click:"You're doing great at this!")[But we're not done just yet.
<img src = "https://i.makeagif.com/media/11-02-2016/bN0MzQ.gif">
That was a tricky one. Although you haven't yet moved on to the therapy plan, you've set the groundwork for understanding John's unique experience. 
He is feeling a sense of loss and grief due to his decline in physical abilities, exhausted by the medical system, and overwhelmed by the financial burden of restoring some of his physical abilities. 
By acknowledging that you believe John's situation is genuienly overwhelming, you have validated his emotional experience. 
Continue.]
(click:"Continue")[You/Sherlock: (text-colour:yellow)["It must be very overwhelming to have such drastic changes to your life happen so suddenly."]
John Watson: (text-colour:green)["It is... ...I just want to get better."] 

How should you respond? 

Option 1 - [["You've come to the right place. That's what we do here."|UnsuccessfulB31]]
Option 2 - [["I'd like to help you with your recovery. I understand you also have some financial concerns and I'd like to discuss that with you and find if there's a way I can make that easier for you too. How would you feel about this?" |Completed]]
Option 3 - [["I can't make any guarantees, but i can help you to get better if you'll let me. There are finance plans available, or you can get a loan if you need." |UnsuccessfulB31]]] 


:: Completed {"position":"1200,1200","size":"100,100"}
Great work! 
(click:"Great work!")[You've avoided overwhelming John and reduced the burden he feels by offering to collaboratively address his problems of concern, and seeking his approval/response to this offer, opening the door to a person-centred plan through empowered decision-making.
Continue
<img src = "data:image/jpeg;base64,"> ]
(click:"Continue")[Remember, not everyone will feel comfortable talking and opening up about their problems like John, and we're not always going to be as clear-thinking as Sherlock Holmes. 
It's important to acknowledge your faults and limitations, forgiving others as well as yourself, and to recognise that all people are experiencing their lives from their own unique POV unable to understand your experiences and life-history the same way that you have experienced them. What may seem significant to me may still be insignificant to you. 

"The worst thing that's ever happened to you, is still the worst thing that's ever happened to you." 
<img src = "https://64.media.tumblr.com/87606b9057f3a4d399f0aa292405d309/tumblr_inline_p87h6jTIL81sen6h4_500.gif">
[[Continue to Final Page|Successful]] ]


